# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ZITO MONOREPO — ENVIRONMENT SETUP GUIDE
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# This is a monorepo with three separate workspaces:
# 1. backend/       - NestJS API (Node.js)
# 2. frontend/      - Next.js web portal (Node.js)
# 3. zito-mobile/   - Expo/React Native mobile apps (JavaScript/TypeScript)
#
# Each workspace has its own .env file and configuration.
#
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ===========================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ===========================================================================
#
# 1. BACKEND SETUP
#    cd backend
#    cp .env.example .env
#    # Edit .env with your credentials (DATABASE_URL, JWT_SECRET, etc.)
#    npm install
#    npm run dev
#
# 2. FRONTEND SETUP
#    cd frontend
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#    # Edit .env.local with your API URL (NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL)
#    npm install
#    npm run dev
#
# 3. MOBILE SETUP
#    cd zito-mobile
#    cp .env.example .env
#    # Edit .env with your API URL (EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL)
#    npm install
#    npm start
#
# ===========================================================================

# No root-level .env needed — each workspace manages its own environment.

